A. PROBLEM STATEMENT :

Design a Low-Level Design for Splitwise – an expense sharing application.

Requirements:

Users can create an account.
Users can create a group and add other users as members.
Users can add expenses within a group.
Support equal split (most common use case). Other splits (exact, percent) can be extension.
The system should automatically calculate who owes whom and maintain a simplified balance.
Users should be able to view overall balances or balance of a specific user.
Users should be able to "Settle Up" with another user (clear the debt).
The design should be clean, extensible.

Constraints:

In-memory implementation is acceptable for LLD.
Focus on core functionality (Equal split in groups).

